title: The Pasta Queen
des:
The Pasta Queen by Nadia Caterina Munno is an entertaining yet real insight into classic Italian recipes and food culture.

Bio: I am Italian, born and raised in Rome. My great great great grandparents owned a pasta factory in the south of Italy. I love making pasta and I specialize in sauces. I grew up with my grandparents making wine and enjoying fresh foods from our lands. I can vividly remember the first time I made fresh pasta with my grandmother Caterina, at age 6. 

I believe that cooking is a lot of technique and a sprinkle of magic... my favorite quote from Fellini.... ‚Äúlife is a combination of magic and pasta‚Äù.

It always tastes better when you are gorgeous in the kitchen üòâ
